This page is a supplementary teaching scaffold for tracked assets.

## Core concept

The compiler can record semantic path use without deciding where a project builder should emit a file.

## Beanstalk boundary

Compiler metadata preserves path use and source context.

The HTML builder decides:

- whether a path becomes an asset
- its route-relative output path
- deduplication
- conflict and warning policy

The build system writes the resulting output records and scopes stale cleanup to the correct manifest owner.

Tracked assets do not live in executable HIR and are not copied directly by a target lowerer.

## Rewrite focus

Explain separation between semantic facts, artefact policy and filesystem side effects.

Canonical details live in both architecture authorities.
